Citation.sTitle: (Vapor + liquid) equilibrium of binary mixtures formed by N,N-dimethyl formamide with some compounds at 95.1 kPa
Citation.sAbstract: Bubble point temperatures (at 95.1 kPa) over the entire composition range are measured for the binary mixtures formed by N,N-dimethyl  formamide with: anisole, 2-cyanopyrazine, n-decane, diisopropyl ether, methyl ethyl ketone and n-octane, making use of a Swietoslawski type  ebulliometer.Wilson equation is used to represent the measured liquid phase composition versus bubble point temperature data. Computed values  of the activity coefficients, vapor phase mole fractions and excess Gibbs energy are tabulated and discussed.
sAuthor: Prasad, T. E. V.[T. E. Vittal]
